    • Method Detail

      • invokeServiceAndGetJson

        String invokeServiceAndGetJson()
                        throws MiddlewareException
        Invokes the service and returns middleware response as JSON String. When an exception is thrown, the result will be added as an attribute to the request object provided to the service request builder. It can be access as request.getAttribute(MWConstants.CHUNKED_RESULTS_IN_JSON) which will return JSON string
        Returns:
        middleware response JSON as a string
        Throws:
        MiddlewareException

      • invokePassThroughServiceAndGetEntity

        org.apache.http.entity.BufferedHttpEntity invokePassThroughServiceAndGetEntity()
                                                                        throws MiddlewareException
        Invokes a response pass through enabled services and returns the BufferedHttpEntity which will contain backend response.
        Returns:
        BufferedHttpEntity that will contain the data received from backend
        Throws:
        MiddlewareException

      • invokePassThroughServiceAndGetEntity

        <R> R invokePassThroughServiceAndGetEntity(Function<InputStream,R> typeParser)
                                    throws MiddlewareException
        Invokes a response pass through enabled service. This method will use the TypeParser passed to it to parse the actual InputStream response from the pass through service and return the response.
        Parameters:
        typeParser - The type parser to be used where R is the type of response to be returned
        Returns:
        Converted object based on TypeParser
        Throws:
        MiddlewareException

      • invokeServiceAndGetResult

        Result invokeServiceAndGetResult()
                          throws MiddlewareException
        Invokes the service and returns middleware response as Result object. When an exception is thrown, the result will be added as an attribute to the request object provided to the service request builder. It can be access as request.getAttribute(MWConstants.RESULTS) which will return result object.
        Returns:
        Middleware Result object for the service invoked
        Throws:
        MiddlewareException
        See Also:
        Result

        Parameters:

        Throws:
